Named after the Munchkins in the Wizard of Oz, the Munchkin breed was accidentally found by a teacher in Louisiana who found two short-legged pregnant cats under her car in the early 1980s.  It is speculated that all Munchkins can be traced back to these two cats.  

Munchkins are known for their short legs, affectionately, playfulness, and cleverness. Commenters on Pepy mentioned that the short legs look really cute when playing and that they are very social cats, making them the perfect pets.
